null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"I've found a node package called `node-source-map-support` that inconveniently uses a `////# sourceMapURL=foo.js.map` [in their file](https://github.com/evanw/node-source-map-support/blob/313c03883ec48dd99cdf43fc9457d40d9599c142/source-map-support.js#L113). On its own, this is not an issue, but when using rollup it produces an invalid file because the next line is being commented out.\r\n\r\n**main.js**\r\n```javascript\r\n////# sourceMappingURL=foo\r\nvar val = 42;\r\nconsole.log(val);\r\n```\r\n\r\n**output**\r\n```javascript\r\n'use strict';\r\n\r\n//var val = 42;\r\nconsole.log(val);\r\n```\r\n\r\n[Take a look.](http://rollupjs.org/?version=0.36.0&)\r\n\r\nInterestingly enough, when using CRLF as newline character, it doesn't remove the newline. Whereas only using LF as newline character, it does get removed. I assume that there's a regex being too greedy?","closed_by":{"login":"Rich-Harris","id":1162160,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExNjIxNjA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1162160?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris","html_url":"https://github.com/Rich-Harris","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Rich-Harris/received_events","type":"User","user_view_